<!-- Where possible please include a self-contained code snippet describing your bug: -->

```py
import enum
from typing import Optional

from pydantic import Field, BaseModel


class Color(enum.Enum):
    red = "red"
    blue = "blue"


class Toaster(BaseModel):
    color: Color
    optional_color: Optional[Color]
    optional_color_2: Optional[Color] = Field(None)
    optional_color_3: Optional[Color] = Field(Color.blue)


print(Toaster.schema_json(indent=2))
```

generates the following json schema:

```json
{
  "title": "Toaster",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "color": {
      "$ref": "#/definitions/Color"
    },
    "optional_color": {
      "$ref": "#/definitions/Color"
    },
    "optional_color_2": {
      "$ref": "#/definitions/Color"
    },
    "optional_color_3": {
      "default": "blue",
      "allOf": [
        {
          "$ref": "#/definitions/Color"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "color"
  ],
  "definitions": {
    "Color": {
      "title": "Color",
      "description": "An enumeration.",
      "enum": [
        "red",
        "blue"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

Everything seems right, except the superfluous `allOf` for `optional_color_3`. It seems related to #1209.
